abstract: Although the weather was nothing to boast of yesterday, it proved a disguised blessing in the observance of the Fourth. abstract: CHICAGO, July 7. -- Provisions were quite animated in speculative circles to-day. There was good outside buying and shorts were quite nervous. Lard and Ribs were bullish from the opening to the close, there being a net gain established in the former amounting to 7 1/2c, while in Rib futures there was an advance of 12 1/2@15c. The Pork market ruled quiet and did not follow the other articles, but closed a trifle easier.

abstract: WASHINGTON, July 22. -- Capt. Henry F. Picking, Chief Hydrographer of the Navy, received an interesting ice report to-day from the Captain of the German steamship Slavonia.
